            "task_description": "<div class=\"collapsible collapsible--text\">\n<p>A 2-hour exam consisting of questions relevant to each of major lecture topics: mood disorders, anxiety and obsessive compulsive disorders, psychotic disorders, substance use disorders, trauma and stressor related disorders, eating disorders, psychopharmacology, personality disorders, and/or other topics to be advised.</p>\n<p>The exam questions will be short answer open-ended and will assess knowledge and understanding of diagnostic classifications, theoretical models, course and basic treatment and management recommendations for adult psychopathology acquired primarily through the workshop program. The exam will be held in the exam period. Practice exam questions are provided during the course and optional multiple choice quizzes will be available after each workshop for you to test your knowledge.</p>\n<p>Please see the course manual for additional instructions. Further information will be provided about the timing and format of the exam during class time.</p>\n<button class=\"collapsible__toggle\">\n<span class=\"collapsible__open link--icon icon--standard--arrow-down-1\">Read full task description</span>\n<span class=\"collapsible__close link--icon icon--standard--arrow-up-1\">Hide full task description</span>\n</button>\n</div>",
